note.p:
Pub. L. 97–35, title XVII, § 1723, Aug. 13, 1981, 95 Stat. 759, as amended effective Oct. 1, 1982, by Pub. L. 97–216, title I, § 101, July 18, 1982, 96 Stat. 189, provided that: “Notwithstanding section 2401(c) of title 39, United States Code, the amount authorized to be appropriated under such section shall not exceed— “(1) $696,000,000 for fiscal year 1982;
“(2) $708,000,000 for fiscal year 1983; or
“(3) $760,000,000 for fiscal year 1984.”
